Here is the Graphviz code to represent the state diagram of the attack:
```graphviz
digraph attack {
    rankdir=LR;
    node [shape=box, style=rounded, fontsize=10];

    AnonymizingServices [label="1. Anonymizing Services (TOR, VPN) usage"];
    SSRFAttack [label="2. SSRF attack & access to private server"];
    WAFMisconfiguration [label="3. WAF misconfiguration"];
    ObtainTemporaryCredentials [label="4. Obtain temporary credentials"];
    ListingS3Buckets [label="5. Listing all S3 Buckets"];
    DataExfiltration [label="6. Data exfiltration from S3 buckets"];

    AnonymizingServices -> SSRFAttack;
    SSRFAttack -> WAFMisconfiguration;
    WAFMisconfiguration -> ObtainTemporaryCredentials;
    ObtainTemporaryCredentials -> ListingS3Buckets;
    ListingS3Buckets -> DataExfiltration;
}
```
To visualize the graph, paste this code into an online Graphviz renderer like [Graphviz Online](https://dreampuf.github.io/GraphvizOnline/) or use the Graphviz software on your local machine.
